        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 7:26PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 726 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bristol, or 15 miles east of Lamar, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Granada, Hartman, and Bristol.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
